      },
      "date": "2012-11-21 19:56:35.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThe second patch resolve an issue with variables based on host identification. The host_id function changed only.\nFor host names which have a dash symbol the caching variable hasn't been evaluated, for example, for the host machine-name.domain the id value was MACHINE-NAME_DOMAIN and the variable name was IS_LOCAL_MACHINE-NAEM_DOMAIN correspondingly.\n\nNow identification switched to md5 signature so we can avoid appearing of dashes, underscore, and other symbols, for example, localhost will have caching variable IS_LOCAL_b8419160170a41ae01abab13a3b887df.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
